scenario: Late-morning foot traffic on the Sentosa promenade: visitors amble between viewpoints and kiosks, navigating around a triangular construction zone to the northwest and a closed block to the east.
Early-evening promenade strolls at Sentosa: families window-shop, take photos, and circulate gently through the open plaza.
Morning cross-traffic of resort staff and joggers cutting across the plaza between the northern boardwalk and southern seating terraces.
A guided wheelchair tour moves from the northern drop-off to the sea-view terrace near the south, with escorts pacing the group.
A mobility clinic practices controlled rolling and assistance routines at the central plaza with cones and markers.
Assisted elderly passengers queue for a shuttle at the east-central pick-up bay while caretakers guide them in.
A school group walks together from the northern entrance to a group-photo spot near the southwest seating area.
A corporate team-building cohort moves as one toward a central activity station set up in the main plaza.
A guided tour group follows a flag-bearing guide to the east-side viewpoint while keeping tight formation.
A busker performance pops up in the central open area; spectators drift in to watch and mill about.
A colorful parade rolls along the southern promenade, with onlookers clustering near the route and drifting between its ends.
A lion dance draws a lively crowd in the north plaza near the boardwalk, with viewers circulating between nearby vantage points.
Pop-up game booths open at two nodes; visitors cluster to play and move back and forth between them.
Race registration tents are set up in the central plaza; participants queue and disperse to collect kits and check maps.
A hands-on craft workshop opens near the northwestern plaza, drawing small groups to participate in short sessions.
A rowdy group gathers near the central walkway; shoving and heated exchanges cause turbulent motion toward the hotspot.
Pushing and jostling intensify near the east corridor as two clusters compete for space by the viewpoint.
A heated confrontation erupts near the southern photo spot; bystanders are drawn in and movement becomes erratic.
A small protest rally assembles at the west-central plaza with chants and banners as supporters converge from multiple directions.
A march gathers near the north plaza before moving along the promenade; participants congregate at the assembly point.
An environmental sit-in forms in the central plaza; demonstrators cluster tightly around speakers and placards.
A fire alarm is triggered at the facade of the large east-side building; people flee away from that side into open areas.
A sudden storm cell approaches from the northwest side; visitors rapidly seek shelter toward central and southern covered areas away from the approach.
A suspected gas leak is reported near the center; staff evacuate visitors toward northern and southern open zones.
Overcrowding builds at the northern entry node as multiple groups arrive at once, creating a tightly packed area.
A night market squeezes the southern promenade, with stalls drawing dense footfall along the bottom edge.
A bottleneck forms in the east corridor where temporary fencing narrows the passage, causing heavy crowding.
A limited-time flash sale is announced at a kiosk near the northeast; people break into a dash toward the offer.
A shuttle arrives at the southwest pick-up; late guests jog and sprint to catch it.
A fireworks preview cue is called at the central lawn; visitors rush to secure good sightlines.
An explosion occurs near the central plaza; people immediately flee toward distant open areas.
A violent clash breaks out at the west-central plaza; bystanders run away toward safer open zones.
A blast near the east corridor sends the crowd sprinting away toward the northwestern and southern exits.
